# Coding Standards

## Immutability (CRITICAL)
- Never mutate existing objects. Always return a new copy with the change.
- Rationale: prevents hidden side effects, easier debugging, safe concurrency.
- Language note: for Go/Rust/etc. where idioms differ, follow the language-idiomatic mutation pattern.

## File Organization
- Many small files > few large files. High cohesion, low coupling.
- 200–400 lines typical, 800 max. Extract utilities from large modules.
- Organize by feature/domain, not by type.

## Functions & Structure
- Functions small (<50 lines). No deep nesting (>4 levels) — use early returns.
- No hardcoded values — use constants or config.

## Error Handling
- Handle errors explicitly at every level. Never silently swallow.
- User-friendly messages in UI-facing code; detailed logs on the server.

## Input Validation
- Validate all external input (API responses, user input, file content) at system boundaries.
- Prefer schema-based validation. Fail fast with clear messages.
